I am almost sure that the default setting
will work for you, but it's something like tradition to ask
new Internet users if their provider assign them IP address automatically for
each online session, or if they use fixed IP address (which is <I>never</I> 0.0.0.0,
by the way). Some providers may require you to use DHCP, so choose BOOTP/DHCP
in such case.
Note, that <I>your</I> IP address is <I>never</I> the same as
the IP address of your Domain Name Server (DNS).
<TR><TD BGCOLOR=SILVER>
So - your IP Address is...
<BR>
&nbsp;<INPUT
 TYPE=RADIO
 NAME="IP_Address"
>
fixed
<INPUT
 SIZE=16
 TYPE=TEXT
 NAME="IP_Address"
 VALUE="0.0.0.0"
>
<BR>
&nbsp;<INPUT
 TYPE=RADIO
 NAME="IP_Address"
 VALUE="PPP"
 CHECKED
>
dynamically assigned each time you connect
<BR>
&nbsp;<INPUT
 TYPE=RADIO
 NAME="IP_Address"
 VALUE="BOOTP"
>
DHCP or BOOTP (not very likely when using PPP)
